There is a separate page for MusicPlayers.

Modes and setups to help you write and perform music:

* EmacsLive is a setup to help you run [http://overtone.github.io/ Overtone], "an open source audio environment designed to explore new musical ideas from synthesis and sampling to instrument building, live-coding and collaborative jamming" based on [http://clojure.org/ Clojure] and using the [http://supercollider.github.io/ SuperCollider] server

* SuperCollider is a mode helping you to write !SuperCollider code directly

* [http://chuck.cs.princeton.edu/ ChucK] Mode by Kao Cardoso FÃ©lix, based on code by Mikael Johansson, is [https://bitbucket.org/kaofelix/chuck-mode available from Bitbucket]

* [https://github.com/repl-electric/sonic-pi.el sonic-pi.el] A Emacs plugin to enable live coding music in Ruby communicating with [http://sonic-pi.net/ SonicPi]
